<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Acting Secretary of State to
                        the Ambassador in Greece (
                        MacVeagh
                    )</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945v03</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d1141</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">1141</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-12-29T20:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-12-29T20:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-12-29T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-12-29T20:00:00-05:00" n="1141" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1141">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 EW/12–2445</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Greece</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-29T20:00:00-05:00">December 29, 1945—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1306. ReEmbtel 38 from Paris to Athens Dec 24, repeated to Dept as 7337. Please
                    make representation to FonOff as suggested by Angell urging Greek Govt to sign
                    final act Paris Conference on Reparation, if possible, before Jan 5. Dept making
                    similar representation Greek Ambassador here.<note n="18" xml:id="d1141fn18">Department’s telegram 2381, December 29, 7 p.m., to Cairo, not printed,
                        urged that similar representations be made to the Egyptian Government
                        (740.00119 EW/12–2445).</note>
                </p>
                <p>Sent to Athens as 1306, repeated to Paris as Depts 6085 for Angell No. 120.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
